column1: #Text=Dublin mayor suggests not sending Irish representative to Israel for Eurovision 2019 ; two European Parliament lawmakers support boycott
#Text=On Sunday , Dublin 's Lord Mayor Mícheál MacDonncha spoke about not sending Irish representatives to the next year 's Eurovision Song Contest , asserting Palestine solidarity .
#Text=The announcement came just one day after Israeli singer Netta won this year 's Eurovision in Portuguese capital Lisbon .
#Text=Two European Parliament lawmakers from Ireland , Lynn Boylann and Nessa Childers , endorsed boycotting next year 's contest .
#Text=Speaking to news site Dublin Live , MacDonncha said next year 's contest should be boycotted to display solidarity with Palestineans .
#Text=" I do n't think we should send a representative " , the mayor said .
#Text=" I think the horrific ordeal of the Palestinian people needs to be highlighted " , MacDonncha said .

#Text=After winning this year 's contest , 25-year-old Netta , who performed Toy featuring chicken dance , chicken noises , and Japanese cultural references criticized as cultural appropriation , said , " Thank you for celebrating diversity .
